column26:
+*_Agile Manifesto Web Platform Project_*+

As part of our software engineering course, we teamed up to create a web-based platform all about the Agile Manifesto. The goal? To help users learn, interact with, and explore Agile values and principles in an engaging way.

This wasn’t just about building a website—it was about living Agile. We broke the project into manageable pieces, worked in Sprints, and embraced feedback to improve along the way.

The final platform includes:

* A sleek homepage introducing the Agile Manifesto.
* Interactive pages that explain Agile values and principles with real-world examples.
* A resource library packed with helpful guides, templates, and a search feature.
* Collaboration tools like a discussion forum and commenting system with user accounts.

Through this project, we learned how to plan, adapt, and work together using Agile methodologies. It was a hands-on experience that showed us the power of teamwork and continuous improvement.
